<body style="margin:0;padding:0;background-color:#ffffff;font-family:-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;color:#27272a;">
  <div style="max-width:600px;margin:0 auto;padding:32px 20px;">
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Hey,</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">Day 10. The toolkit. The goal is not to own every HVAC tool; it is to have the tools that match your actual install path.</p>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">Useful on almost every DIY install</h2>
    <ul style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 18px 24px;padding:0;">
      <li>Cordless drill and bits for mounting equipment and disconnect hardware.</li>
      <li>Level for wall brackets, pads, and condensate slope.</li>
      <li>Tube cutter and deburring tool for clean copper cuts.</li>
      <li>Torque wrench for flare fittings where the manufacturer specifies torque.</li>
      <li>Multimeter for confirming voltage and dead circuits.</li>
      <li>Foil HVAC tape, closed-cell insulation, fasteners, and condensate-drain materials.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2 style="font-size:17px;color:#18181b;margin:28px 0 10px 0;">Only for certain projects</h2>
    <ul style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.7;margin:0 0 18px 24px;padding:0;">
      <li>Manifold gauges, vacuum pump, refrigerant scale, and recovery tank: only if you are legally and practically doing non-pre-charged refrigerant work.</li>
      <li>Sheet-metal tools: only if you are modifying ductwork.</li>
      <li>Airflow meter: useful for diagnostics, but not a substitute for a real commissioning visit.</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0 0 16px 0;">The most expensive mistake is buying pro-grade tools for a one-time task that would cost less to hire out. Price the tool, the learning curve, and the cost of getting it wrong.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:0;">Day 21 is the equipment-path email: pre-charged mini-splits, single-zone versus multi-zone, and what to watch before ordering.</p>
    <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;margin:20px 0 4px 0;">&mdash; NailTheQuote</p>
